<h3 style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">TRIMA | TMA</span></h3>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><script type="text/javascript">DukascopyApplet = {"type":"chart","params":{"showUI":true,"showTabs":false,"showParameterToolbar":true,"showOfferSide":true,"allowInstrumentChange":true,"allowPeriodChange":true,"allowOfferSideChange":true,"showAdditionalToolbar":false,"showExportImportWorkspace":true,"allowSocialSharing":false,"showUndoRedoButtons":false,"showDetachButton":false,"presentationType":"candle","axisX":true,"axisY":true,"legend":false,"timeline":false,"showDateSeparators":true,"showZoom":true,"showScrollButtons":true,"showAutoShiftButton":true,"crosshair":true,"borders":false,"freeMode":false,"theme":"Default","uiColor":"#000","availableInstruments":"l:","instrument":"BTC/USD","period":"5","offerSide":"ASK","timezone":0,"live":true,"allowPan":false,"indicators":"sDYFRJRAQRIQZAFUMKPgAgInFLidyQHFkHSJCXUAGEAGgBp6AamVGACpsOzbBvaXiMMSqAPAjTFIGqCM","width":"100%","height":"275","adv":"popup"}};</script><script type="text/javascript" src="https://freeserv-static.dukascopy.com/2.0/core.js"></script></span></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square; text-align: left;">
<li id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-6" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">The triangular moving average (TMA or TRIMA) is an average of an average, of the last N prices (P).</li>
<li id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-8" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">First, calculate the <a title="simple moving average (SMA)" href="https://www.thebalancemoney.com/simple-exponential-and-weighted-moving-averages-1031196" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">simple moving average (SMA)</a>:</li>
<li id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-10" class="ql-syntax">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>SMA = (P1 + P2 + P3 + P4 + ... + PN) / N</strong></em></li>
<li id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-12" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">Then, take the average of all the SMA values to get TMA values.</li>
<li id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-13" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;<em>TMA = (SMA1 + SMA2 + SMA3 + SMA4 + ... SMAN) / N</em></strong></li>
<li id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-15" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block">&nbsp;The TMA can also be expressed as: TMA = SUM (SMA values) / N</li>
<li class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">font: <a title="The Balance Money" href="https://www.thebalancemoney.com/triangular-moving-average-tma-description-and-uses-1031203">The Balance Money</a></li>
</ul> <hr />
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">KAMA |Kaufman Adaptive Moving Average</span></h4>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><script type="text/javascript">DukascopyApplet = {"type":"chart","params":{"showUI":true,"showTabs":false,"showParameterToolbar":true,"showOfferSide":true,"allowInstrumentChange":true,"allowPeriodChange":true,"allowOfferSideChange":true,"showAdditionalToolbar":false,"showExportImportWorkspace":true,"allowSocialSharing":false,"showUndoRedoButtons":false,"showDetachButton":false,"presentationType":"candle","axisX":true,"axisY":true,"legend":false,"timeline":false,"showDateSeparators":true,"showZoom":true,"showScrollButtons":true,"showAutoShiftButton":true,"crosshair":true,"borders":false,"freeMode":false,"theme":"Default","uiColor":"#000","availableInstruments":"l:","instrument":"BTC/USD","period":"5","offerSide":"ASK","timezone":0,"live":true,"allowPan":false,"indicators":"sDYaRARBUxZoQADMCbiuwDcFuJrrgiPAADyA6gAxNgxx3l_xdgAD6MNmb7qHqBkAfIBMAIfwH_FQmg..","width":"100%","height":"275","adv":"popup"}};</script><script type="text/javascript" src="https://freeserv-static.dukascopy.com/2.0/core.js"></script></span></p>
<h4 id="formula" style="text-align: left;">ATR Formula and Calculations <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><br /></span></h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Kama uses <a title="EMA Stock Scanner" href="https://www.marketvolume.com/stockstradingsystems/?d=54&amp;aid=Exponential-MA">EMA</a> formula with the difference of EMA coefficient. Below you may see the formula for Exponential Moving Average:<br /><strong>EMA = Alpha * (Price - Pervious EMA) + Previous EMA</strong><br />where <strong>Alfa = 2 / (P + 1)</strong> and where <strong>P</strong> is&nbsp; a bar period selected by a user.<br />Kaufman Adaptive Moving Average uses the same formula:<br /><strong>KAMA = Alpha * (Price - Pervious KAMA) + Previous KAMA</strong><br /><strong>Alpha</strong> is calculated here in different to the traditional EMA way. Alpha is based on the Fast Coefficient (FC) and Slow Coefficient (SC) - the same as with <a title="MACD Calculator" href="https://www.marketvolume.com/stocks/macd.asp?s=XLF&amp;t=financial-select-sector-spdr">MACD</a>, to calculate KAMA a user selects fast and slow bar periods<br /><strong>FC = 2 / (FP + 1) </strong>and where <strong>FP</strong> is Fast Period selected by a user<br /><strong>SC = 2 / (SP + 1)</strong> and where <strong>SP</strong> is Slow Period selected by a user<br />In addition, <strong>Alpha</strong> depends on the <strong>Efficiency Ratio</strong>:<br /><strong>ER = Change / Sum of absolute changes</strong><br />Where "<strong>Change</strong>" is calculated as the change over selected by a user bar period and "<strong>sum of absolute changes</strong>" is calculates as sum of absolute changes of each bar in this selected period. In many cases, Efficiency Ratio is calculated over the Slow Period which is used to calculate Slow Smoothing. <br /><strong>Alpha = (ER * (FC - SC) + SC)^2</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">By <em><a href="https://plus.google.com/103915293292544776925/about" rel="author">V. K.</a></em> for MarketVolume.com</p>
<hr />
<h3 style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Awesome Oscillator Indicator (AO)</strong></span></h3>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><script type="text/javascript">DukascopyApplet = {"type":"chart","params":{"showUI":true,"showTabs":false,"showParameterToolbar":true,"showOfferSide":true,"allowInstrumentChange":true,"allowPeriodChange":true,"allowOfferSideChange":true,"showAdditionalToolbar":false,"showExportImportWorkspace":true,"allowSocialSharing":false,"showUndoRedoButtons":false,"showDetachButton":false,"presentationType":"candle","axisX":true,"axisY":true,"legend":false,"timeline":false,"showDateSeparators":true,"showZoom":true,"showScrollButtons":true,"showAutoShiftButton":true,"crosshair":true,"borders":false,"freeMode":false,"theme":"Default","uiColor":"#000","availableInstruments":"l:","instrument":"BTC/USD","period":"5","offerSide":"ASK","timezone":0,"live":true,"allowPan":false,"indicators":"sDYQROVBaEAC2CfguALGFDADgCEMbIDhKnaM6zACDsADqAYQEcACtgGwM8CULQPAEgx7ZUAnVhdEKDCoLOC5VLQqAegOMMDKFgtMgKg8FAoophK0wMXGYMsOWcF0ig..","width":"100%","height":"275","adv":"popup"}};</script><script type="text/javascript" src="https://freeserv-static.dukascopy.com/2.0/core.js"></script></strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The <strong>Awesome Oscillator Indicator (AO)</strong> is a technical analysis indicator created by American trader Bill Williams as a tool to determine whether bullish or bearish forces dominate the market. It measures the market momentum with the aim of detecting potential trend direction or trend reversals. The market momentum is evaluated using a combination of a shorter time frame and longer time frame simple moving averages; in other words, it considers the recent momentum in comparison with a higher frame momentum.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The Awesome Oscillator strategy is calculated as the difference between the newest five periods (bars) simple moving average (SMA) and the 34 bars simple moving average. But instead of the closing price, the indicator uses the bar midpoint value. Although it may look like the Awesome Oscillator formula is complex, it&rsquo;s really quite simple, as shown below:</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Midpoint value = (Bar high &ndash; Bar low) / 2</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Awesome Oscillator = SMA5 &ndash; SMA34</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The indicator is plotted as a histogram in a box at the bottom of the chart and the histogram bars are found in either of the two colours red or green (with some trading platforms, the lines can be red or blue). When the midpoint value of the last price is higher than the previous bar midpoint, the histogram is green (blue) and if the midpoint of the last bar is lower compared to the previous bar, it is red.</p>
